18. When dried, they could see their subjects<lb/>
clearly before their eyes, almost half-painted.<lb/>
Then, they put down the other layers<lb/>
in one sitting, with a singular effort and skill.<lb/>
They did not apply paint in very thick layers,<lb/>
but in a thin light, delicate manner, <lb/>
always brilliant and clean,<lb/>
by drawing fine white hairs, as in life.<lb/>

