<ab>
20. They were very attentive to this refinement,<lb/>
and placed their colors beautifully, neat and fresh.<lb/>
They did not load their panels as we do now, <lb/>
so that with eyes closed, one could touch<lb/>
and perceive the work almost everywhere.<lb/>
For in our time, the paint is applied to be<lb/>
so uneven and rough, that one would think<lb/>
they are almost reliefs sculpted in stone.<lb/>
</ab>

<ab><margin>right-middle</margin>On the roughness of some in these times.</ab>
</div>

<div>
<id>p048r_5</id>

<ab>
21. Neatness is praiseworthy, for it nourishes<lb/>
the gaze by holding it for a long time,<lb/>
especially if it is held with naturalness,<lb/>
intelligence and boldness, and always looks<lb/>
correct no matter if seen from a distance or up close.<lb/>
Such things attract one; while the eyes<lb/>
are insatiable, the heart cleaves to it with pleasure.<lb/>
</ab>

<ab><margin>right-middle</margin>Clean subjects, which preserve intelligence, are praiseworthy, and hold the viewer’s gaze for a long time.</ab>
</div>

